<p>Getting started is pretty easy, assuming you already have Node.js installed:</p>

<pre>
$ git clone https://github.com/akashacms/akashacms-example.git -b akasharender
$ cd akashacms-example
$ npm install
$ .... start hacking
$ npm run build
$ npm run preview
</pre>

<p>This pulls down site full of examples for you from the <a href="https://github.com/akashacms/akashacms-example">akashacms-example</a> project.  For a blank starter site look at <a href="https://github.com/akashacms/akashacms-skeleton">akashacms-skeleton</a>.  <strong>akashacms-skeleton HAS NOT YET BEEN CONVERTED</strong> </p>

<p>The skeleton starter site can also be initialized this way: </p>

<pre>
$ git clone https://github.com/akashacms/akashacms-skeleton.git -b akasharender
$ cd akashacms-skeleton
$ npm install
$ .... start hacking
$ npm run build
$ npm run preview
</pre>

<p>To build the static website:</p>

<pre>
$ npm run build
</pre>

<p>To view the local copy of the website in your browser (http://localhost:3000):</p>

<pre>
$ npm run preview
</pre>
